    "body": "Hi @alexandraB99 the transfer ownership flows are now ready for development. I can setup a call with whoever is picking this up to go through but below is an overall summary:\r\n\r\nThe Community Settings / Overview screen has been tidied up and now contains a control node banner. There are 2 states for the banner:\r\n\r\n1) Where the user's device is the control node - in this instance, the banner copy relates to keeping the control node online and has the CTA to `Move control node`\r\n\r\n2) Where the user's device is not the control node (this could be a Community admin or the owner who is on a different device)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"1\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/5bb7dfc7-d6c1-483c-a788-609682c703e1\">\r\n\r\nIn both states of the banner, there is a `Learn more` link which links to our Status documentation on control nodes - the link for this is stipulated in the designs.\r\n\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\n\r\n**If the user's device IS the control node**\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"2\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/3fe9dbf0-b2a8-401e-8dad-c12202333f5c\">\r\n\r\nWhen the user clicks `Move control node` they authenticate (given the subsequent dialog reveals the Community private key). \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"4\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/da27e668-3692-4c07-8171-7288873f3510\">\r\n\r\nOnce authenticated the user can copy the private key, check the relevant acknowledgements and finally `Delete private key and stop control node`. After this, the Community overview screen shows a toast confirming that the device is no longer the control node. The control node banner state is flipped - the copy and buttons are now focused on the reverse action - making the device the control node.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"5\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/d8a20c83-28b1-4886-80bf-e47f255991cb\">\r\n\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**If the user's device is NOT the control node**\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"3\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/8c7332ee-1991-4a82-b25d-f25ef9fbdc2f\">\r\n\r\nWhen the user clicks `Make this device the control node` we check if there are existing control nodes. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"6\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/97b566d4-9fcb-4ea7-9105-9c9d3c27a382\">\r\n\r\nIf so an amber warning shows, clarifying to the user that there are other devices acting as the control node for the Community and that running multiple control nodes will cause issues. The user is not blocked from entering the private key and becoming the control node however. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"7\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/e0224154-1493-4b4b-ad24-012c8ba04ea1\">\r\n\r\nOnce the user has entered the private key for the Community, the key is checked and validated and if it is the correct private key for that Community, we enable the button `Make this device the control node for [Community name]`. This triggers authentication (only if needed from a dev perspective). A toast is shown over the Community overview page confirming the user's device is now the control node. The control node banner is switched to the variant that requests the user keep the device online and shows the button to `Move control node`\r\n\r\n\r\nFigma designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=31171-630010&t=IIt7pohtmgc4Y7G6-4\r\n\r\n\r\nThis work also impacts the following:\r\n\r\n**Community overview** screen designs which are updated and added to the Kuba file here. Note designs have also been done to show how this resizes down to 1200px.\r\n\r\nKuba designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=31229-627216&t=IIt7pohtmgc4Y7G6-4\r\n\r\n\r\n**Import Community via private key** flows. These are featured in the Kuba file and \r\n\r\nKuba designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=2878-383500&t=IIt7pohtmgc4Y7G6-4\r\n\r\nSettings design files:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/idUoxN7OIW2Jpp3PMJ1Rl8/%E2%9A%99%EF%B8%8F-Settings-%7C-Desktop?type=design&node-id=16038-386359&t=1TzOQTNzTJoIq7P9-4\r\n\r\n\r\ncc @John-44 ",
